{"id":"263281446_Pattern-avoiding_permutations_and_Brownian_excursion_Part_I_Shapes_and_fluctuations","abstract":"Permutations that avoid given patterns are some some the most classical\nobjects in combinatorics with strong connections to many fields of mathematics,\ncomputer science and biology. In this paper we study the scaling limits of a\nrandom permutation avoiding a pattern of length 3 and their relations to\nBrownian excursion. Exploring this connection to Brownian excursion allows us\nto strengthen the recent results of Elizalde [13], Madras and Pehlivan [25] and\nMiner and Pak [29] as well as to understand many of the interesting phenomena\nthat had previously gone unexplained.","authors":["Christopher Hoffman","Douglas Rizzolo","Erik Slivken"],"meta":["June 2014Random Structures and Algorithms 50(3)","DOI:10.1002/rsa.20677","SourcearXiv"],"references":["301843407_Pattern_Avoidance_for_Random_Permutations","45902700_A_unification_of_permutation_patterns_related_to_Schubert_varieties","41448325_Conditional_limit_theorems_for_branching_processes","37598300_Statistics_on_pattern-avoiding_permutations","2942109_Multiple_Pattern_Avoidance_with_Respect_to_Fixed_Points_and_Excedances","2140556_On_the_Distribution_of_the_Length_of_the_Longest_Increasing_Subsequence_of_Random_Permutations","2105017_Fixed_Points_and_Excedances_in_Restricted_Permutations","2095727_Kazhdan-Lusztig_Polynomials_for_321-Hexagon-Avoiding_Permutations","279957910_Sums_of_Independent_Random_Variables","268934910_An_introduction_to_combinatory_analysis","268442261_Essay_d''Analyse_sur_les_Jeux_de_Hazard","266909814_Brownian_motion_With_an_appendix_by_Oded_Schramm_and_Wendelin_Werner","265492750_Random_pattern-avoiding_permutations","262493823_The_Art_of_Computer_Programming","261144645_Foundations_of_Modern_Probability","259893424_Structure_of_Random_312-Avoiding_Permutations","259845421_Patterns_in_Random_Permutations_Avoiding_the_Pattern_132","243780456_Asymptotic_theory_of_characters_of_t